<task id="AIPU-020" project="spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r1">
  <metadata>
    <title>Output pane registry + widgets 1-4 (BudgetDashboard, SearchResults, AnalysisEditor, ContractComparison)</title>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <phase>2</phase>
    <wave>2</wave>
    <estimated-effort>5 hours</estimated-effort>
    <tags>shared-library, frontend, fluent-ui, output-widgets</tags>
    <parallel-safe>false</parallel-safe>
    <dependencies>003</dependencies>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Implement the output pane widget registry and the first four output widgets for the @spaarke/ai-outputs library. This task owns the registry file and widgets 1-4 only. Widget files 5-8 are owned by task AIPU-021 and widget files 9-11 are owned by AIPU-031 — do not create or modify those files here.

    Deliverables:
    1. src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Outputs/src/types/widget-types.ts — OutputWidgetType enum, SourceWidgetType enum, and shared interfaces (IOutputWidget, ISourceWidget, WidgetRegistryEntry, OutputWidgetProps, SourceWidgetProps). These types are shared with tasks 021 and 022.
    2. src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Outputs/src/registry/output-registry.ts — lazy registry that maps OutputWidgetType string keys to dynamic import() factories. Exported as outputWidgetRegistry.
    3. BudgetDashboardWidget.tsx — renders a financial budget summary with spend vs. budget bars using Fluent v9 ProgressBar.
    4. SearchResultsWidget.tsx — renders a list of ranked search result cards with title, excerpt, and relevance score badge.
    5. AnalysisEditorWidget.tsx — renders a markdown analysis body with section headings, supports edit mode toggle.
    6. ContractComparisonWidget.tsx — renders a two-column diff view comparing two contract clauses with highlighted delta lines.

    All widgets receive data via their props (no direct API calls inside widgets). Widget data is passed from the AI streaming response already parsed by the calling code page.
  </prompt>

  <role>Senior frontend developer with expertise in React 19, Fluent UI v9, and shared component library authoring</role>

  <goal>
    A fully typed, lazy-loaded output widget registry and four working output widgets (BudgetDashboard, SearchResults, AnalysisEditor, ContractComparison) exported from @spaarke/ai-outputs, with zero hard-coded colors, full dark mode support, and TypeScript compilation passing.
  </goal>

  <relevant-files>
    <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Outputs/src/types/widget-types.ts</file>
    <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Outputs/src/registry/output-registry.ts</file>
    <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Outputs/src/output-widgets/BudgetDashboardWidget.tsx</file>
    <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Outputs/src/output-widgets/SearchResultsWidget.tsx</file>
    <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Outputs/src/output-widgets/AnalysisEditorWidget.tsx</file>
    <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Outputs/src/output-widgets/ContractComparisonWidget.tsx</file>
    <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Outputs/src/registry/source-registry.ts</file>
    <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Outputs/src/index.ts</file>
    <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/index.ts</file>
    <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/package.json</file>
  </relevant-files>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-021">All widgets must use Fluent v9 makeStyles with design tokens only. No hard-coded hex colors, no inline style={{ color: '#...' }}. Dark mode must work via FluentProvider theme switching without any additional code in widgets.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-012">@spaarke/ai-outputs is a shared library. Every public component and type must be exported from src/index.ts. Follow the barrel export pattern from @spaarke/ui-components.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">NOT PCF-safe. Widgets may use React 19 features (useTransition, etc.) freely. Do not gate on React 16/17 compatibility.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Registry pattern: output-registry.ts maps OutputWidgetType enum values to lazy factories: () => import('./WidgetName'). Registry must not eagerly import any widget module at startup.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Widget props must be typed via OutputWidgetProps&lt;T&gt; generic from widget-types.ts. Each widget defines its own data shape T.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Do not create widget files 5-8 (TimelineWidget, DocumentCompareWidget, DataTableWidget, ChartWidget) — those are owned by task AIPU-021.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Do not create widget files 9-11 (StatusSummaryWidget, RecommendationWidget, ActionPlanWidget) — those are owned by task AIPU-031.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Do not create source widget files — those are owned by task AIPU-022.</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>docs/adr/ADR-012-shared-components.md</file>
      <file>docs/adr/ADR-021-fluent-design-system.md</file>
      <file>.claude/constraints/react-versioning.md</file>
      <file>.claude/constraints/theme-consistency.md</file>
      <file>.claude/patterns/shared/shared-library-build.md</file>
      <file>docs/guides/ai-assistant-theming.md</file>
    </files>
    <patterns>
      <pattern name="Shared library barrel exports" location="src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/index.ts">
        All public components and types re-exported from a single index.ts. Follow this pattern for ai-outputs index.ts.
      </pattern>
      <pattern name="Fluent v9 makeStyles" location="src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/PanelSplitter/PanelSplitter.tsx">
        Use makeStyles from @fluentui/react-components. Tokens from tokens.colorNeutral*, tokens.spacingHorizontal*, etc. No hard-coded values.
      </pattern>
      <pattern name="Lazy registry" location="src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Outputs/src/registry/output-registry.ts">
        Registry shape: Record&lt;OutputWidgetType, () =&gt; Promise&lt;{ default: React.ComponentType&lt;OutputWidgetProps&lt;unknown&gt;&gt; }&gt;&gt;
        Populated with dynamic import() per widget. No eager imports.
      </pattern>
    </patterns>
  </knowledge>

  <steps>
    <step>Read src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/index.ts and package.json to understand library export conventions.</step>
    <step>Read src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Outputs/src/types/index.ts (scaffold from task 003) and src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Outputs/src/registry/output-registry.ts to understand what already exists.</step>
    <step>Create or replace src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Outputs/src/types/widget-types.ts:
      - OutputWidgetType enum: BudgetDashboard, SearchResults, AnalysisEditor, ContractComparison, Timeline, DocumentCompare, DataTable, Chart, StatusSummary, Recommendation, ActionPlan
      - SourceWidgetType enum: DocumentViewer, WebSource, LegalLibrary, Citation, ImageViewer, CodeViewer
      - OutputWidgetProps&lt;T&gt;: { data: T; isLoading?: boolean; error?: string; className?: string }
      - SourceWidgetProps&lt;T&gt;: { data: T; isLoading?: boolean; error?: string; className?: string }
      - WidgetRegistryEntry&lt;T&gt;: { type: string; label: string; factory: () =&gt; Promise&lt;{ default: React.ComponentType&lt;T&gt; }&gt; }
      Export all types.</step>
    <step>Create src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Outputs/src/registry/output-registry.ts:
      - Import OutputWidgetType from types/widget-types.ts
      - Define outputWidgetRegistry as Record&lt;OutputWidgetType, () =&gt; Promise&lt;...&gt;&gt; using dynamic import() for all 11 widgets
      - Export outputWidgetRegistry and a helper resolveOutputWidget(type) that calls the factory and returns the default export.</step>
    <step>Create src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Outputs/src/output-widgets/BudgetDashboardWidget.tsx:
      - Props: OutputWidgetProps&lt;{ title: string; items: Array&lt;{ label: string; spent: number; budget: number; currency: string }&gt; }&gt;
      - Render title, then a list of ProgressBar (Fluent v9) rows with spent/budget label
      - Use makeStyles for layout, tokens for colors.</step>
    <step>Create src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Outputs/src/output-widgets/SearchResultsWidget.tsx:
      - Props: OutputWidgetProps&lt;{ query: string; results: Array&lt;{ id: string; title: string; excerpt: string; score: number; url?: string }&gt; }&gt;
      - Render query header, then Card list. Each card: title as Link (if url), excerpt text, Badge for score percentage.
      - Use makeStyles. Fluent v9 Card, Badge, Link, Text.</step>
    <step>Create src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Outputs/src/output-widgets/AnalysisEditorWidget.tsx:
      - Props: OutputWidgetProps&lt;{ sections: Array&lt;{ heading: string; body: string }&gt;; editable?: boolean }&gt;
      - Render each section as a Fluent v9 Title3 + Body1 block. If editable and edit mode active, replace body with Textarea.
      - Toggle edit mode via local useState. Save button calls optional onSave prop.
      - Use makeStyles.</step>
    <step>Create src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Outputs/src/output-widgets/ContractComparisonWidget.tsx:
      - Props: OutputWidgetProps&lt;{ leftLabel: string; rightLabel: string; clauses: Array&lt;{ id: string; left: string; right: string; hasDelta: boolean }&gt; }&gt;
      - Render two-column layout (CSS grid 1fr 1fr) with each clause pair. Delta lines highlighted using tokens.colorStatusWarningBackground3.
      - Use makeStyles.</step>
    <step>Update src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Outputs/src/index.ts to export:
      - All types from types/widget-types.ts
      - outputWidgetRegistry and resolveOutputWidget from registry/output-registry.ts
      - BudgetDashboardWidget, SearchResultsWidget, AnalysisEditorWidget, ContractComparisonWidget (named exports)</step>
    <step>Run TypeScript compilation check: cd src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Outputs &amp;&amp; npx tsc --noEmit to confirm zero errors.</step>
  </steps>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion>src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Outputs/src/types/widget-types.ts exists with OutputWidgetType and SourceWidgetType enums, OutputWidgetProps and SourceWidgetProps generics, and WidgetRegistryEntry type — all exported.</criterion>
    <criterion>output-registry.ts exports outputWidgetRegistry with lazy dynamic import() factories for all 11 output widget types. No widget module is imported at the top of the file.</criterion>
    <criterion>BudgetDashboardWidget.tsx renders Fluent v9 ProgressBar rows for each budget line item with spent vs. budget values.</criterion>
    <criterion>SearchResultsWidget.tsx renders a Card list with title, excerpt, and relevance score Badge for each search result.</criterion>
    <criterion>AnalysisEditorWidget.tsx renders sections with headings and body text; supports optional edit mode via Textarea.</criterion>
    <criterion>ContractComparisonWidget.tsx renders two-column clause comparison with delta rows highlighted using Fluent v9 warning color tokens.</criterion>
    <criterion>All four widgets use makeStyles with Fluent v9 design tokens only — no hard-coded hex colors, no inline style color values.</criterion>
    <criterion>All four widgets and all exported types are re-exported from src/index.ts.</criterion>
    <criterion>TypeScript compilation passes with zero errors (npx tsc --noEmit).</criterion>
    <criterion>Widget files 5-8, 9-11 and all source widgets are NOT created by this task.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
